/SCD/XXERASH/XX. The willow has no smell or taste; the myrtle has smell but not
taste; the palm, taste but not smell; the /ITetrog/XX, both smell and taste. In the
/ITlulav/XX all are united, each is necessary; even the lowliest is required to bring
out the worth of all./PR
/PR
The sight and smell of these four species help us celebrate the bounteous
diversity of nature and remind us that we are responsible for preserving
the conditions that make their growth possible. Human life requires the
flourishing of trees: the divine presence in the interdependence of species./PR
/PR
We hold these diverse species together as a reminder that the diversity in
the world comprises the elements of its unity. So can we discover the unity
in human life.    /SC/XXD.A.T./XX/PR
